 Port Elizabeth - Flower Reserve, Woodridge, Blue Horizon Bay, East London, Mthatha and Fort Beaufort received much of the rains that fell across the Eastern Cape overnight on Thursday. This is according to the latest rainfall figures released by the South African Weather Service office in Port Elizabeth. 2020/02/01 Station Names 28 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 3.2 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 12.0 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 18.4 ARS Chatty 3.6 AWS Coega 3.2 AWSH Fettes Road 8.8 ARS Flower Reserve 29.8 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 6.8 ARS St Albans 11.2 AWS Uitenhage 14.2 MAN Woodridge 33.7 Catchment  AWS Joubertina 2.4 ARS Kareedouw 6.6 Man Kareedouw 9.0 Man Kouga Dam 6.5 AWS Patensie 18.0 Man   Other Towns  AWS Addo 9.4 AWS Bisho/KWT 13.0 AWS Cape St Francis 2.2 AWS Cradock 0.2 AWS East London 22.0 AWS Fort Beaufort 15.4 AWS George 0.3 AWS Graaff Reinet NIL AWS Grahamstown 3.6 AWS Henry`s Flats * AWS Joubertina 2.4 AWS Mossel Bay 7.0 AWS Mthatha 16.6 AWS Plettenberg Bay * AWS Port Alfred 11.2 AWS Queenstown 0.8 * no contact 0.0 = Drops  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 